From Steve Manes Subject Re Drinking and Riding Norman Hamer wrote What is a general rule of thumb for sobriety and cycling Couple hours after you feel sober What Or should I just work with If I drink tonight I don't ride until tomorrow It depends on how badly you want to The FAA says eight hours bottle to throttle for pilots but recommends twenty four The FARs specify a blood alcohol level of as legally drunk I think which is more than twice as strict as DWI BTW alcohol metabolizes in your blood at a fixed rate one beer hour will keep your blood alcohol level barely street Coffee hyperventilation and other bar tricks won't speed it up nor will they fool Stephen Manes Manes and Associates New York NY USA o o